    <note>Yu(9) Shi [17639] Chen Liang, WJ, 28.7b-8b, 29.4b-5a (reburial inscription for wife, born Wang(2), who was the sister of He(2) Ju's [17658] wife). A son-in-law, Zhao(1) Ti (not in dataset), has the same generational name as the sons of Zhao(1) Xiaozong [9011], which may or may not indicate an imperial connection. Shi did receive an official title by imperial grace. A grandson, Kan [17646], is identified in CBD, 4, 1965 as a nephew of Yu(9) Liangneng [17648]. Liangneng was a son of Baoguang [17649] (q.v.), who was, therefore, either a brother or cousin of Shi--I am assuming that Baoguang was brother and therefore a son of Shi's father, Deng [17638]. CBD, 4, 2965.</note>
